uk.co.strangeskies.utilities

Class ForwardingListener<T,U>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.ForwardingListener<T,U>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of event message to consume
    U - The type of event message to produce
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Consumer<T>, Observable<U>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AggregatingListener, BufferingListener, LatestListener

    public abstract class ForwardingListener<T,U>
extends Object
implements Consumer<T>, Observable<U>
    A buffer to decouple the delivery of events with their sequential consumption, such that the event firing threads are not blocked by listeners.

    Consumed events are translated to produced events by way of an implementation of ForwardingListener.Buffer, the implemented methods of which are guaranteed to be invoked synchronously.
